<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--TreeTheft     12-10 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Tree Theft,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Outdoor Christmas Tree Stolen, Lights and All</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 7-foot-tall living Christmas tree in
Charles and Arlene Heraly's front yard is gone _ lights and all.
   Vandals chopped down and carried off the spruce that the Heralys
had treasured for a decade since their three children gave it to
them.
   Police said Friday they have no suspects in Wednesday's theft.
   ``We all watched it grow,'' Arlene said. ``It means so much to
us.''
   Each year at this time Heraly, 74, and his 72-year-old wife set
up a life-sized Nativity scene next to the tree. Each Christmas Eve,
a life-sized infant Jesus is placed in the manger. The honor of
placing the model in the manger has passed from their nine
grandchildren to their three great-grandchildren.
   ``It wouldn't mean so much if it hadn't been given to us,'' Mrs.
Heraly said.
</TEXT>
