<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Italy-Lion Attack,0145</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lions Kill Caretaker, Young Helper</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GALLARATE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pair of lionesses kept in a farmhouse
in northern Italy escaped from their cage and killed their caretaker
and a helper.
   Esmerina Scotti, 62, was looking after the animals that belonged
to brother while he was in the hospital, police said.
   The retired railway worker was fond of wild animals and had kept
lions for several years.
   But when his sister noticed Friday that the lions were not in
their cage, she telephoned an 18-year-old friend, Marcello Cerutti,
who had a lion of his own, for help.
   One of the lions, hidden behind a car, attacked the woman, then
turned on the young man.
   The lions were later captured by police and firefighters.
   Police said many people in the rural area near Milan raise wild
animals.
</TEXT>
