<HEAD>Thief Steals Last Item from Going-Out-Of-Business Store</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YORK, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tired of shoplifters who preyed on his business,
Donald Flinchbaugh closed the store and auctioned off every item _
except one.
   On Tuesday, someone stole it.
   A thief swiped a $1,000 cash register as buyers picked up items
they bought during the public auction Dec. 3 at the former Ole Toll
Gate Super Thrift Store. The register was the only item not sold
during the auction.
   Flinchbaugh, who owned the store for two years, said he closed
his business Oct. 29.
   ``There was too much shoplifting and too much stealing,'' he said
at the York Township police station. ``It was too much. I'm glad I'm
out of it.''
