<HEAD>Pope Offers Money And Prayers For Armenia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II today offered condolences
and $100,000 to victims of the deadly earthquake in the Soviet
republic of Armenia.
   ``I express to your excellency, to the Soviet people and
particularly to the entire Armenian nation, the feelings of my
spiritual closeness and suffering,'' the pontiff said in a telegram
to Soviet President Mikhail Gorbachev.
   The pope also offered his prayers for all of the Soviet Union.
