<2ND_LINE>AM-Hotel Fire,0192</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Dead in Extra-Alarm Hotel Fire in Middletown, Ohio</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIDDLETOWN, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire in a two-story apartment-hotel
Saturday night killed three people and injured one, authorities said.
   All of the 20 firefighters on duty in the southwestern Ohio city
and a number of off-duty personnel were called in to fight the blaze
at the Baltimore Inn, said assistant Fire Chief Roger South.
   ``We're still fighting it. They've got a lot of fire down
there,'' South said about an hour and a half after the fire was
reported around 7 p.m.
   The building housed a hotel, tavern and restaurant. The three
people who were killed and the one who was injured were believed to
be the only ones remaining in the building when police arrived, a
police dispatcher said.
   The identities of the victims and the cause of the fire were not
immediately known, South said.
   The injured person was taken to Middletown Regional Hospital. A
nursing supervisor said the victim did not appear to be badly hurt,
but was being examined.
   Middletown is a city of about 45,000 north of Cincinnati.
</TEXT>
