<1ST_LINE>u a AM-BuriedBodies 1stLd-Writethru a0610 12-10 0355</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Buried Bodies, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0610,0360</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Arrest Man In Death Linked To Landlady Dorothea Montalvo
Puente</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Rewrites throughout to add background, location of town,
estimated age of Sutter County victim; delete redundant material in
third graf pvs; add that two more bodies identified Friday. No
pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A body found nearly three years ago in
Sutter County has been linked to Dorothea Montalvo Puente, the
landlady already a suspect in the deaths of seven people whose
bodies were found around her rooming house, police said.
   Police arrested Ismael Carrasco Florez on Saturday and said he
built a wooden box and helped Puente put a body in it and deposit it
in Sutter County nearly three years ago.
   Capt. Michael O'Kane said no more information about Florez will
be made available until a Sunday morning news conference.
   A decomposed female body about 55 years old was found by a farm
worker on New Year's Day 1986 along the Sacramento River near the
town of Verona, about 15 miles northeast of Sacramento. The body was
wrapped in plastic.
   Police on Friday said they were working with Sutter County
sheriff's deputies concerning the body because of similarities in
the way it and the seven bodies unearthed in Puente's rooming house
yard were wrapped.
   Puente, charged with one count of murder, is in the county jail.
Last month, police dug up seven bodies from the yard of the downtown
Victorian house where she took in elderly, disabled or alcoholic
tenants.
   Police say Social Security and welfare checks sent to boarders
who were missing were nevertheless cashed.
   On Friday, police disclosed the identities of two more victims,
both former tenants of Puente. That brings to four the number of
victims who have been identified.
   The bodies of Dorothy Miller, 65, and Vera Martin, 65, were
identified through medical X-ray evidence, said O'Kane. Identified
earlier were Ben Fink, 55, and Alvaro ``Bert'' Montoya, 52. Puente
has been charged with homicide in Montoya's death.
   Sacramento police say they have not yet been able to determine
the cause of death for any of the seven.
</TEXT>
